<Author>skhakoo
<Content>Great location, Good Value, Clean Rooms, Lacking Customer Service Just returned from a 4 night stay in Beijing at the Red Wall. Let's begin with the positives. Location, location, location. On the footsteps of the Forbidden City and a beautiful park, around the corner from the ancient hutong alleyways where locals still live, one block from a street food court and two large supermarkets and literally doors away from an absolutely delicious muslim chinese eatery (serving barbeque beef and naan bread).The hotels rooms were spacious and clean. Our beds were more like doubles than twins. The bathrooms had a nice variety of free toiletry. The lobby was clean and inviting. The beauty salon was first rate. The breakfast was included in our plan and it had a larger than average variety of western cuisine as well as chinese cuisine. One staff person made fresh dumpling soup based on the spice needs of the customer.Now to the not so good. The customer service lacked in every respect. Changing money was limited to $300 per day. We had a really hard time having them take our travelers checks claiming signature mismatch. Getting service at the counter felt like a chore each day.So for the simple traveller with no real need for customer service and happy with a great location and good value, this hotel is for you. The service lacked and it ruined an otherwise great stay in a fabulous location. 
